spans.text: Miss Danae , when Fair and Young ( As Horace has divinely sung )
from Jove's Embrace By Doors of Steel

himself sincere and hearty : For , give That Whipster but his Errand ; He takes my Lord Chief Justice's Warrant : Dauntless as Death away He walks ; Breaks the Doors open ; snaps the Locks ; Searches the Parlour , Chamber , Study ; Nor stops , till He has Culprit's Body
the Bolt , the Bar Make Us less Curious , Her less Fair
This Friend nor Eye , nor Heart
chain Him to a hated Trust
all this mingled Mass , which She Being forbidden
the fat Bawd , and lavish Heir The Spoils of ruined Beauty share
Where the fat Bawd , and lavish Heir The Spoils of ruined Beauty share : And Youth seduced from Friends and Fame , Must give up Age to Want and Shame
all her Ways be unconfined : And clap your Padlock — on her Mind
